    <p>
        - When the environment is hot and dry plants lose water faster.<br>
        - It is therefore important to reduce the surface area so they lose less water or store 
        water in their tissues, with some plants doing both.
    </p>
    <Table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Plant</th>
                <th>How it changes surface area</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>Cacti</td>
                <td>Some plants like cacti have broad leaves with a large surface area.
                    The leaves collect dew at night and funnel the water towards the base 
                    of the plant to the root system. The leaves then close during the daytime 
                    to reduce water loss.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Ferns</td>
                <td>Some plants like ferns have curled leaves to reduce the surface area.
                    The leaves trap a layer of moist air around the leaf to reduce the amount
                    of water that the plant loses through evaporation. </td>
            </tr>
